  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urgent Support to Returning Undocumented Afghans</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under the auspices of IOM Afghanistan&apos;s long running Cross Border Return and Reintegration (CBRR) programme, the objective of this project is to reduce the vulnerability of undocumented Afghan returnees through the provision of life-saving humanitarian assistance as defined under the 2019 Afghanistan Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP). In order to achieve this, IOM is providing post-arrival assistance to returning Afghans at border crossings with the Islamic Republic of Iran and Pakistan while strengthening medical screening and related services at transit center health posts. In addition, IOM plans to deploy two mobile health teams within local communities affected by return and displacement and to contribute to increased knowledge of population flows and through the continued roll out of IOM&apos;s Displacement Tracking Matrix to ensure evidence-based assistance delivery.</narrative>
  </description>
